        "synopsis": {
            "value": "Chae Yong-Joo (Kim Se-Jeong) is a former member of the special forces in the military. She has strong physical strength, strong mental fortitude and her own unique cheerfulness. She is also good at hiding her true emotions. She now works as a salesperson for a liquor company. She has worked at the company for 6 years and has obtained the title of the sales king. She is very devoted to her work and the branch where she works, but the branch is on the verge of closing. To avoid the closure, she carries out a mission. Her mission is to sell a new beer. That beer is made by brewmaster & CEO of the brewery company Yoon Min-Joo (Lee Jong-Won). He is a sensitive man and good at sensing other people's emotions. He lives in a peaceful and quiet rural area to focus on making beer and his emotions, but Chae Yong-Joo appears in front of him. This changes his life.\n\nMeanwhile, Bang A-Reum (Shin Do-Hyun) is a manager of the planning team. She competes with Chae Yong-Joo for Yoon Min-Joo’s brewery. Oh Chan-Hwi (Baek Sung-Chul) is Chae Yong-Joo’s friend with a free-spirit.",
